        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "A vendor bid is a bid made on behalf of the vendor to stimulate competition or move bidding toward the reserve. Under Queensland's Property Occupations Act 2014, vendor bids are permitted, but the auctioneer must announce each vendor bid clearly as a vendor bid before making it. Vendor bids cannot be made once the reserve price has been met."
      }
